		<div>Dell now owns Alienware, so maybe somewhere in the mix there is some uniformity.  Video card I would definitely use anything Nvidia as ATI has the worlds worst customer support as well as driver support.<br />
<br />
Here is the link to get to Alienware if  you want to make  your one decisions.  I have never heard anything bad about the performance of the Alienware products, but I would definitely take what Ewan said and Heiken said into consideration as well.  The best decisions are always the ones you make on the greatest amount of info you can get whether it is reliable or not the more info  you get the more you can attest to the reliability of any one piece of info.  Good Luck and let us know which one you get.  Personally I would not be concerned with encumbrence if your thinking about performance.  I would definitely prefer to lug around the extra weight if it meant getting the performance and screen size that I wanted.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.alienware.com/configurator_pages/aurora_m9700.aspx?sssdmh=dm11.91898&amp;syscode=PC-LT-AURORA-M-9700&amp;subcode=SKU-AD" target="_blank">http://www.alienware.com/configurat...&amp;subcode=SKU-AD</a><br />
